==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: bigeminate
<hw>bi*gem"i*nate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>geminate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having a forked petiole, and a pair of leaflets at the end of each
division; biconjugate; twice paired; -- said of a decompound
leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bigential</ent>⟦br⟧
